<header>
	<h1>Site Builder</h1>
</header>

<section class="dash-content-section">

	<section>
	<h2>What is Site Builder?</h2>
	<p>Build your website using Twig templates with automatic URL routing. Create pages in the sidebar, define routes and templates, and your site is live immediately &mdash; no generation step needed.</p>
	</section>

	<section>
	<div class="builder-stats">
		<div class="stat-grid">
			<div class="stat-item">
				<span class="stat-number">{{ builder.pages|length }}</span>
				<span class="stat-label">Pages</span>
			</div>
			<div class="stat-item">
				<span class="stat-number">{{ fileTree.layouts|length }}</span>
				<span class="stat-label">Layouts</span>
			</div>
			<div class="stat-item">
				<span class="stat-number">{{ fileTree.pages|length }}</span>
				<span class="stat-label">Templates</span>
			</div>
			<div class="stat-item">
				<span class="stat-number">{{ fileTree.partials|length }}</span>
				<span class="stat-label">Partials</span>
			</div>
			<div class="stat-item">
				<span class="stat-number">{{ fileTree.macros|length }}</span>
				<span class="stat-label">Macros</span>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	</section>

	<section class="builder-info">
		<h3>Configuration</h3>
		<table class="admin-table">
			{% if builder.docroot %}
			<tr>
				<td>Docroot</td>
				<td><code>{{ builder.docroot }}</code></td>
			</tr>
			{% endif %}
			<tr>
				<td>Assets Path</td>
				<td><code>{{ builder.assetsPath }}</code></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td>Pages Collection</td>
				<td><code>{{ builder.pagesCollection }}</code></td>
			</tr>
		</table>
	</section>

	{% set assets = builder.assets %}
	{% set totalAssets = assets.css|length + assets.js|length + assets.fonts|length + assets.images|length + assets.other|length %}
	<section>
		<h3>Frontend Assets</h3>
		{% if totalAssets > 0 %}
		<p>Files in <code>{{ builder.assetsPath }}/</code> available via <code>cms.builder.css()</code>, <code>cms.builder.js()</code>, and <code>cms.builder.asset()</code>.</p>

		{% if assets.hasManifest %}
		<p><strong>Manifest detected</strong> &mdash; hashed filenames will be resolved automatically.</p>
		{% endif %}

		<table class="admin-table">
			{% if assets.css is not empty %}
			<tr>
				<td>CSS</td>
				<td>
					{% for file in assets.css %}
						<code>{{ file }}</code>{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}
					{% endfor %}
				</td>
			</tr>
			{% endif %}
			{% if assets.js is not empty %}
			<tr>
				<td>JavaScript</td>
				<td>
					{% for file in assets.js %}
						<code>{{ file }}</code>{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}
					{% endfor %}
				</td>
			</tr>
			{% endif %}
			{% if assets.fonts is not empty %}
			<tr>
				<td>Fonts</td>
				<td>
					{% for file in assets.fonts %}
						<code>{{ file }}</code>{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}
					{% endfor %}
				</td>
			</tr>
			{% endif %}
			{% if assets.images is not empty %}
			<tr>
				<td>Images</td>
				<td>{{ assets.images|length }} file{{ assets.images|length > 1 ? 's' : '' }}</td>
			</tr>
			{% endif %}
			{% if assets.other is not empty %}
			<tr>
				<td>Other</td>
				<td>{{ assets.other|length }} file{{ assets.other|length > 1 ? 's' : '' }}</td>
			</tr>
			{% endif %}
		</table>
		{% else %}
		<p>No assets found in <code>{{ builder.assetsPath }}/</code>. Place your CSS, JavaScript, fonts, and images there to reference them in templates with <code>cms.builder.css()</code> and <code>cms.builder.js()</code>.</p>
		{% endif %}
	</section>

	<section>
	<h3>Getting Started</h3>
	<ol>
		<li>Create a <strong>layout</strong> in <code>layouts/</code> with your base HTML structure</li>
		<li>Create <strong>page templates</strong> in <code>pages/</code> that extend your layout</li>
		<li>Click <strong>+ New Page</strong> to add pages with routes, templates, and metadata</li>
		<li>Use <code>cms.builder.nav()</code> in your nav partial to generate navigation</li>
		<li>Add CSS and JS to <code>{{ builder.assetsPath }}/</code> and load them with <code>cms.builder.css()</code> and <code>cms.builder.js()</code></li>
	</ol>
	</section>

</section>
